impression: Loading of a user generated and placed impression pixel for the purpose of creating an attributing event from a marketing effort. By this definition, no automated renders from Branch (e.g. Journeys, Deepviews) are impressions, nor are views of content in the app.
click: A user initiated action of tapping on a Branch link or html element directly in front of a Branch link
web to app auto redirect: A web to app auto redirect works by simulating the action of a user clicking a link, but without user interaction. Technically this is implemented using "open_app=true" in our web to app products. Currently, this only exists on Journeys (+ banners + Web SDK Deepviews).
branch cta view: The loading of a visual element or webpage that includes a Branch-created CTA, powered by a Branch link. Today, this includes loading Journeys and Deepviews.
sms sent: An successfully triggered call to send an SMS (not necessarily receipt of the SMS)
open: A mobile app launch that is not an install (ie not a first time app launch for that persona). An "open" ends when an app is backgrounded or closed.
install: The first time an app launches for a given IDFA/AAID. (Excludes cases where the IDFA is reset with the app still installed.)
reinstall: When an app is deleted then re-installed on the same device (same device is defined as same IDFA/AAID).
web session start: A 'web session start' event occurs the first time a user visits the site within a specific tab of their browser. After that, when a user is browsing within the same tab, the WebSDK will only fire a 'web session start' on page load if there is a _branch_match_id query param in the URL (the user was referred to the page by a Branch link).
pageview: A pageview is the loading of a single page for a given website which is triggered more specifically, by calling branch.init() or branch.track('pageview')
commerce event: A standard event where a customer is on a journey to pay money to a business. It excludes views, but includes adding to cart through to purchasing. [Uses Branch event tracking code or the Data Ingestion pipeline. Each event within it is a point in time action.]
custom event: Custom event is a non-standard user tracked event. [Uses Branch event tracking code or the Data Ingestion pipeline. Each event within it is a point in time action.]
content event: A standard event involving content that may or may not be a product, but excludes events where a customer is on a journey to pay money to a business (adding to cart to purchasing). [Uses Branch event tracking code. Each event within it is a point in time action.]
user lifecycle event: A standard event not involving content. [Uses Branch event tracking code. Each event within it is a point in time action.]
dismissal: A dismissal is the removal/closing of a banner/interstitial/button for a journey view for a given website which is triggered by calling branch.closeJourney (currently used for journey only, could be used for other fieatures as well).
Webhook Record: Upon a webhook firing, a record of that firing including a subset of information about the event that caused it to fire and the success/failure of that request.
